# Core Rules

## ApiClient
- Follow `lib/src/core/api/usage_documentation.md` for all usage patterns
- ❌ Never import or instantiate `Dio` / `http` outside `core/api/`
- Inject `ApiClient` via constructor — never create it ad hoc inside a repository

## StateStatus
`lib/src/core/bloc/state_status.dart` provides `initial | loading | success | error`.
Use this enum for all async status in BLoC states. Only introduce a custom enum if these four values are genuinely insufficient.

## FieldState
`lib/src/core/bloc/states/field_state.dart` — use for every form/input field in BLoC state:

| Field | Type | Meaning |
|-------|------|---------|
| `value` | `T` | Current input value |
| `status` | `FieldStatus` | `pure \| valid \| invalid` |
| `error` | `String?` | Validation message shown below the field when `invalid` |
| `isDirty` | `bool` | `true` after first user interaction |
| `enabled` | `bool` | `false` to disable the field |

## Failure type → UI routing

| `FailureType` | Component | Notes |
|---------------|-----------|-------|
| `snackbar` | `BaseSnackbar.error / .warning / .info / .success` | Default; non-blocking |
| `banner` | `ScaffoldMessenger → MaterialBanner` | Persistent warning |
| `inlineError` | `FieldState.error` below the input | Mapped in BLoC; never via snackbar |
| `alert` | `BaseDialog.showBasic(...)` | Blocking modal; `barrierDismissible: false` |
| `fullScreenError` | `BaseDialog.showFullscreen(...)` | Critical; replaces screen content |
| `silent` | Nothing shown | Log/analytics only |

If `failure.message == null`, show a localized fallback via `context.l10n`.

## Analytics conventions
- Global event names: `lib/src/core/monitoring/analytics/analytics_events.dart`
- Feature-specific events: `lib/src/features/<feature>/domain/analytics/<feature>_events.dart`

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — user_config feature events in domain/analytics/user_config_events.dart
final class SetAppThemeModeUseCaseEvent extends AnalyticsEvent {
  factory SetAppThemeModeUseCaseEvent.success() => ...
  factory SetAppThemeModeUseCaseEvent.failure({required Map<String, dynamic> properties}) => ...
}

// ❌ BAD — hardcoded string outside constants class
Analytics.track(AnalyticsEvent(name: 'theme_changed'));

// ❌ BAD — analytics in BLoC (ThemeBloc, LocaleBloc, etc.)
// analytics only belong in UseCase call() methods
```

- `Analytics.track(...)` is only permitted inside `UseCase.call()` implementations
- `AnalyticsEventNames` and `AnalyticsPropertyKeys` constants must be used — no raw strings
